This paper is about scene labeling, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel approach that involves recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and attention models, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence research. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The paper also involves natural language processing techniques, such as attention models and recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in the field of computational linguistics. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible category. Finally, the paper involves neural networks, which are a type of computational model used in the field of computational neuroscience. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category.
